    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Iran (
                        Murray
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d354</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">354</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-06T05:35:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-06T05:35:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-06T05:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-06T05:35:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/8–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-06T14:00:00+03:25">August 6, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 6—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>590. My telegrams 554, July 28; 560, July 30;<note n="73" xml:id="d354fn73">For
                        Nos. 554 and 560, see <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1395">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Potsdam</hi>), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 1395</ref>
                        and <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1397">1397</ref>, respectively.</note>
                    and 583, August 3. I should greatly appreciate any information and guidance
                    Department can give me regarding agreement apparently reached at Potsdam on
                    withdrawal Allied troops from Tehran especially as it may concern relation of
                    American troop movements to those of British and Soviet forces.</p>
                <p>British Ambassador today asked whether American authorities in Tehran would be
                    prepared to participate in mixed Anglo-Soviet-American Commission to schedule
                    evacuation (my telegram 583, August 3). Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
